    "n_faq_eTwBPR": {
      "type": "n_faq",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_z3H6yi": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How quickly will I see results?",
            "text": "<p>A natural derivative of vitamin A, this hero ingredient speeds up the removal of old skin cells to reveal your best, most rejuvenated skin underneath.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_yfwJdA": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How many patches come per box?",
            "text": "<p>There are 8 pairs per box. We recommend using the Patches 1-2 times per week, which means one box should last you 1 month. </p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_LMGP4E": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long should I apply the patches for?",
            "text": "<p>For optimal results, we suggest applying the patches for a minimum of 2 hours, but preferably overnight.</p><p>Leaving the patches on while you sleep ensures that the serum has ample time to dissolve and penetrate into the skin, maximizing its effectiveness to give you the best results.</p><p>We recommend using 1-2 times per week.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_NMiyy6": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I use the patches while pregnant or breast feeding?",
            "text": "<p>Yes! Many pregnant women avoid injectables, retinols, or any strong acids for anti-aging during this time, so many turn to Qure as a safer alternative. However, we always recommend speaking with a medical professional for advice prior to use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_HXfTge": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are they only suitable for use around the eyes?",
            "text": "<p>The best thing about our Micro-Infusion patches is that you can target different areas of concern. Whether it be under-eyes, crow’s feet, smile lines or frown lines.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "accordion_z3H6yi",
